cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper discusses microarchitectural attacks and cache hierarchies, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. The paper also presents more efficient eviction set profiling and covert channel profiling, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE), systems and control (cs.SY), and programming languages (cs.PL).
